WorkItem.Description:
I was trying to work a bit on my Z80 skills as i encountered a weird thing. For a few months i was happy to get stuff working with Wabbitcode. So i just loaded my code again, did assemble it and wanted to run it with Wabbitmenu z80+ emulator.

Assembling went well, but the emulator just says: ERR:SYNTAX

Even a simple program like this does not work anymore. All is well during assembly. It gives the same error on a real device by the way.

Do i miss anything? I have no clue where to look/start.

```
.nolist
#include "../ti84plus.inc"
#define    ProgStart    $9D95
.list
.org    ProgStart - 2
	.db    t2ByteTok, tAsmCmp
	bcall(_ClrLCDFull)
    
	ld a, 12
	bcall(_PutC); 

	rlca
	bcall(_PutC); 

	RET
    
.end
.end
```
